n a thousand peer-reviewed articles across a wide range of fields documents a startling gap between how academics typically describe good writing and the turgid prose they regularly produce.Stylish Academic Writing showcases a range of scholars from the sciences, humanities, and social sciences who write with vividness and panache. Individual chapters take up specific elements of style, such as titles and headings, chapter openings, and structure, and close with examples of transferable techniques that any writer can master.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aAcademic writing. 0aEnglish languagexStyle. 70(DE-601)1041167490(DE-588)4116621-8aStilistik2gnd 70(DE-601)1061129530(DE-588)4066612-8aWissenschaftssprache2gnd 70(DE-601)1061130110(DE-588)4066596-3aWissenschaftliches Manuskript2gnd 70(DE-601)1063387490(DE-588)4014777-0aEnglisch2gnd 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Authorship.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS AND LITERATURE 2012z978311028890208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2012z978311037491908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674065093423Coveruhttps: